{"coursehistories": {"path": "/coursehistories/404"}, "description": "Writing with a view to publication in the freelance sections of newspapers such as THE PHILADELPHIA INQUIRER and THE NEW YORK TIMES, in magazines such as THE ATLANTIC and THE NEW YORKER, and in the literary quarterlies and the journals of opinion. Among the areas likely to be considered are writing as a public act, issues of taste and of privacy, questions of ethics and of policy, methods of research and of checking, excerpting, marketing, and the realistic understanding of assignments and of the publishing world. Student papers will be the basis of weekly editorial sessions, with concentration on the language: how to render material literate, how to recognize and dispose of padding and self-indulgence, how to tighten structure and amplify substance. \n\nSee the English Department's website at www.english.upenn.edu for a description of the current offerings. \n\n", "semester": "2011C", "name": "ADV NON-FIC WRITING", "reviews": {"path": "/courses/24315/reviews", "values": [{"ratings": {"rAmountLearned": "3.83", "rDifficulty": "2.67", "rStimulateInterest": "3.83", "rRecommendMajor": "3.83", "rCourseQuality": "4.00", "rWorkRequired": "2.33", "rInstructorAccess": "3.67", "rReadingsValue": "3.83", "rRecommendNonMajor": "2.50", "rCommAbility": "4.00", "rInstructorQuality": "4.00"}, "section": {"name": "ADV NON-FIC WRITING", "sectionnum": "301", "primary_alias": "ENGL-145-301", "path": "/courses/24315/sections/301", "id": "24315-301", "aliases": ["ENGL-145-301"]}, "comments": "", "num_students": 7, "path": "/courses/24315/sections/301/reviews/5736-STEPHEN-D-METCALF", "instructor": {"path": "/instructors/5736-STEPHEN-D-METCALF", "first_name": "STEPHEN D", "last_name": "METCALF", "id": "5736-STEPHEN-D-METCALF", "name": "STEPHEN D METCALF"}, "num_reviewers": 6, "id": "24315-301-5736-STEPHEN-D-METCALF"}, {"ratings": {"rAmountLearned": "4.00", "rDifficulty": "2.60", "rStimulateInterest": "3.80", "rRecommendMa